32:31.317 --> 32:33.652
Every day. No clouds, no rain.

32:33.752 --> 32:35.321
God forbid if it hails.

32:35.454 --> 32:37.356
I didn't think of the hail.

32:37.456 --> 32:38.756
They did.

32:38.757 --> 32:41.660
You've got 54 wells
on this property.

32:41.760 --> 32:43.329
Only six produce.

32:43.429 --> 32:46.865
And, hell, none of 'em pump more
than ten or 12 barrels a day.

32:46.965 --> 32:49.235
And I'm 18% of that.

32:50.002 --> 32:53.205
This area is all played out.

32:53.305 --> 32:55.641
For these little
grasshopper pumps, it is.

32:55.741 --> 32:57.843
But they don't go
down 2,000 feet.

32:57.943 --> 32:59.478
They're sucking on a leak.

32:59.578 --> 33:02.648
The shale is 7,000
to 10,000 feet down.

33:02.748 --> 33:04.683
I know,
but ain't nobody gonna invest

33:04.816 --> 33:08.087
in swapping wells
and drilling for 54 wells.

33:09.088 --> 33:12.858
Hell, most of these leases
is expired.

33:12.958 --> 33:15.094
[chuckles, sighs]

33:15.194 --> 33:16.662
I'm sitting on a stack
of minerals

33:16.762 --> 33:18.497
I can't sell
for the paper they're on.

33:18.597 --> 33:21.067
- [chuckles]
- I can.

33:21.900 --> 33:24.002
How you gonna do that?

33:27.139 --> 33:28.440
[Cooper sighs]

33:28.540 --> 33:32.078
This is 377 on 11,000 acres.

33:32.878 --> 33:34.746
Put together 50 acres at a time.

33:34.880 --> 33:37.249
Seven largest are
in the same situation as you.

33:37.349 --> 33:38.884
Four of 'em
have already committed.

33:38.984 --> 33:41.486
But your royalty rate
is not 18% anymore.

33:41.487 --> 33:42.754
It's 25.

33:42.888 --> 33:46.358
Now,
you can wreck that wheat field,

33:46.458 --> 33:48.526
hope to make 200 a year,

33:48.527 --> 33:50.896
or we can rework these wells,
and I can pay you that a month.

33:51.029 --> 33:55.434
You run all the cattle you want.
Who cares what they cost?

33:57.002 --> 33:58.904
That's how it was in the '70s.

33:59.004 --> 34:01.273
- [chuckles]
- Well, power's in the numbers.

34:01.407 --> 34:05.377
A group of small producers
become a big producer.

34:07.313 --> 34:09.715
And just how much
of my 25 do you take?

34:09.815 --> 34:11.682
Not a dime.

34:11.683 --> 34:14.352
You're signing the lease to me,
I'm selling it to them.

34:14.353 --> 34:16.655
Oil company pays me, not you.

34:16.755 --> 34:18.757
That helps you,
and it helps your neighbor.

34:18.857 --> 34:20.626
That's where I'm going next.

34:26.565 --> 34:28.800
What do I got to do?

34:30.236 --> 34:32.271
Just sign the lease.

34:32.404 --> 34:34.440
Then you ain't got
to do nothing.

34:34.540 --> 34:36.442
Neither do your kids
or their kids.

34:36.542 --> 34:37.909
[Swensen scoffs]

34:38.009 --> 34:40.146
Well, they got to do something.

34:40.246 --> 34:41.780
I don't need 'em
hanging around here.

34:41.913 --> 34:44.249
Well, dig 'em a pool.
Let 'em splash around in that.

34:44.250 --> 34:47.453
[scoffs]
A swimming pool?

34:47.553 --> 34:50.756
In Garza County?
[chuckles]

34:51.557 --> 34:53.224
Wouldn't that be something?

34:53.225 --> 34:54.626
[chuckles]

34:54.726 --> 34:56.362
[paper rustling]

34:56.462 --> 35:00.166
Lord help me.
[chuckles]

35:05.604 --> 35:08.807
Well, Cooper,
nice doing business with you.

35:08.907 --> 35:11.242
Thank you very much,
Mr. Swensen.

35:11.243 --> 35:12.777
You won't regret it.

35:12.778 --> 35:14.780
[Swensen]
I hope not.

35:14.880 --> 35:16.848
<i>♪ gentle, atmospheric music ♪</i>

35:17.183 --> 35:19.685
<i>***</i>

35:46.245 --> 35:47.679
[Tommy]
They've been pumping oil

35:47.779 --> 35:49.315
out of this ground
since the '20s.

35:49.415 --> 35:51.149
Then, in the '80s,
it started drying up.

35:51.250 --> 35:53.151
By the '90s
it's pretty well played out.

35:53.252 --> 35:56.222
This is a shale. It goes all
the way from here to Midland.

35:56.355 --> 35:59.691
So just imagine
layer after layer of solid rock

35:59.791 --> 36:02.994
slapped on top of one another
like slices of bread.

36:03.094 --> 36:06.130
And between the slices,
well, that's your butter.

36:06.131 --> 36:08.834
Just figured that out
a few years ago.

36:08.934 --> 36:12.671
Now, Chevron spent
$53 billion dollars

36:12.771 --> 36:15.541
to buy a drilling company
to get it out.

36:15.641 --> 36:19.378
So we can assume the leases
on 400 wells,

36:19.478 --> 36:21.547
but we're gonna have
to drill horizontal

36:21.647 --> 36:23.147
and we're gonna have
to frack it.

36:23.148 --> 36:25.650
A deal like that's called
a farm-out.

36:25.651 --> 36:28.053
So, we have access to 400 wells.

36:28.153 --> 36:30.856
But it's gonna cost between
11 and 18 million dollars

36:30.956 --> 36:31.957
for each well.

36:32.057 --> 36:34.059
We agreed to the first nine.

36:34.159 --> 36:36.228
That's $162 million dollars.

36:36.328 --> 36:38.264
Now, if we hit
on the first four,

36:38.364 --> 36:41.233
that means we're obligated
to drill nine more.

36:41.333 --> 36:43.569
If we hit on four more,
then we're committed to 27.

36:43.669 --> 36:45.103
You see where
I'm going with that?

36:45.203 --> 36:47.072
- I do.
- Our deal

36:47.205 --> 36:50.376
is that we recoup
on strikes to 120%

36:50.476 --> 36:52.176
and then
we start revenue sharing.

36:52.177 --> 36:55.012
It's a pretty good deal
when it's two percent interest.

36:55.013 --> 36:58.516
But at 12%,
we're bankrupt in a month

36:58.517 --> 37:00.752
if it turns out
the first nine are dry holes.

37:00.852 --> 37:03.221
Okay, so what do you want
from me?

37:03.322 --> 37:06.724
Well, each strike has
to pay for itself

37:06.725 --> 37:09.094
and then it has to pay
for the next one.

37:09.194 --> 37:10.829
So we got to get ahead
of the bank.

37:10.929 --> 37:13.063
You have to make a deal
that pays for the whole thing

37:13.064 --> 37:14.766
on the first home run.

37:14.900 --> 37:18.069
Now, Nate here is gonna
take you through the numbers.

37:18.169 --> 37:20.105
Dale will take you
through the science.

37:20.238 --> 37:22.908
By tomorrow
you'll be a damn expert.

37:25.210 --> 37:27.078
Why new pumps?

37:27.178 --> 37:28.614
What's wrong with these?

37:28.714 --> 37:30.748
You mean "wells."

37:30.749 --> 37:31.983
Too shallow.

37:32.083 --> 37:33.251
Well, how deep do they need
to be?

37:33.352 --> 37:34.420
- Dale?
- [Dale] Ah,

37:34.520 --> 37:36.455
between 10,000 and 13,000 feet.

37:36.555 --> 37:38.255
But you got
to drill at an angle,

37:38.256 --> 37:40.191
- and then you got to frack it.
- Frack it.

37:40.292 --> 37:42.994
You shoot a shit ton
of salt water downhole,

37:43.128 --> 37:44.796
and you squeeze all that oil out
of the fractures,

37:44.896 --> 37:47.633
then you pump it up,
separate the water.

37:47.733 --> 37:50.436
Technology...
it changed the game out here.

37:50.536 --> 37:51.937
Yeah, isn't this the technology

37:52.037 --> 37:54.440
that's causing earthquakes
in Oklahoma?

37:55.273 --> 37:57.275
There were earthquakes
in Oklahoma

37:57.376 --> 37:58.644
- before fracking, ma'am.
- Okay.

37:58.744 --> 38:00.479
- Jesus Christ.
- Tommy!

38:01.580 --> 38:03.414
- Yeah?
- Look.

38:03.415 --> 38:05.651
[chuckles]
You understand,

38:05.784 --> 38:07.918
I don't think anyone should be
doing this, all right?

38:07.919 --> 38:09.420
I think it should be illegal.

38:09.421 --> 38:10.989
Well, then,
you should've run for Congress

38:11.089 --> 38:13.325
instead of getting a job
with an oil company.

38:13.459 --> 38:15.292
I just...

38:15.293 --> 38:16.828
I have a very hard time

38:16.962 --> 38:19.665
advocating for something
I believe is wrong.

38:19.765 --> 38:20.999
Says the lawyer.

38:21.132 --> 38:23.369
Good and bad
don't factor into this, Rebecca.

38:23.469 --> 38:25.136
Our great-grandparents
built a world

38:25.236 --> 38:27.839
that runs
on this shit right here.

38:27.939 --> 38:29.475
Until it starts running
on something else,

38:29.575 --> 38:33.745
we got to feed it,
or the world stops.

38:37.315 --> 38:38.917
[truck door opens]

38:41.987 --> 38:44.356
[engine starts]

38:44.456 --> 38:46.658
[Tommy]
Hey.

38:47.593 --> 38:49.126
There is an alternative.

38:49.127 --> 38:51.328
You can throw your phone away
and trade that Mercedes in

38:51.329 --> 38:53.831
for a bicycle or a horse and
start hunting for your own food

38:53.832 --> 38:56.201
and living in a tent,
but you'll be the only one

38:56.334 --> 38:57.968
and it won't make a damn bit
of difference.

38:57.969 --> 39:01.907
Plus I hear the moral high
ground gets real windy at night.

39:17.222 --> 39:19.625
<i>***</i>

39:32.638 --> 39:34.573
<i>♪ pulsing, suspenseful music ♪</i>

39:34.840 --> 39:37.108
<i>***</i>

39:54.993 --> 39:57.529
[engine revs]

40:09.575 --> 40:11.276
[truck doors open]

40:25.457 --> 40:27.459
You were supposed to call me.

40:27.593 --> 40:28.794
It's been one of those days.

40:28.927 --> 40:31.930
I know those days.

40:32.030 --> 40:34.299
You've given me a few.

40:38.637 --> 40:41.640
There's something
I want to show you.

40:41.740 --> 40:43.174
All right, I'll follow you.

40:43.274 --> 40:44.776
How about you ride with me?

40:44.876 --> 40:46.778
How about I follow you?

40:53.318 --> 40:55.721
[grunting]

41:09.334 --> 41:11.336
- [truck door opens]
- [Tommy groans]

41:13.605 --> 41:16.508
[engine starts]

41:16.608 --> 41:19.344
[tires squealing]

41:48.907 --> 41:51.543
[Tommy groaning]

42:03.188 --> 42:04.556
It's quite the view out here.

42:04.656 --> 42:06.692
You bring me
to the nicest places.

42:06.792 --> 42:08.993
[Jimenez scoffs]

42:08.994 --> 42:12.898
You think
oil companies are so strong,

42:12.998 --> 42:16.067
that you can do
anything anywhere.

42:16.167 --> 42:17.569
[scoffs]

42:17.703 --> 42:19.104
I looked it up.

42:19.204 --> 42:21.406
We make more money than you.

42:21.506 --> 42:23.609
Than all of you.

42:24.576 --> 42:26.812
You sell your product
for three dollars a gallon.

42:26.912 --> 42:30.582
A gallon of our product sells
for thousands,

42:30.716 --> 42:32.918
and we can't make enough.

42:33.018 --> 42:35.153
[grunts]

42:36.021 --> 42:37.889
You have an army.

42:37.989 --> 42:40.325
We have an army.

42:44.796 --> 42:48.299
- [groans]
- You blow things up.

42:48.433 --> 42:50.001
We do, too.

42:51.036 --> 42:52.270
[groans]

42:52.370 --> 42:54.039
[snaps fingers]

43:13.291 --> 43:16.361
[metallic creaking]

43:17.428 --> 43:20.131
That tank has a sensor
to trigger an alarm.

43:20.265 --> 43:23.669
One goes to the fire department,
one goes to headquarters.

43:23.769 --> 43:25.269
Helicopters will get here first.

43:25.270 --> 43:28.006
And when they put it out,
which will take about a day,

43:28.106 --> 43:29.607
fucking Railroad Commission

43:29.708 --> 43:32.644
and OSHA will be crawling
over this fucking place

43:32.744 --> 43:34.012
like fucking ants.

43:34.145 --> 43:37.548
And since
they're explosives experts,

43:37.649 --> 43:40.686
they'll know exactly
what this is.

43:40.819 --> 43:44.322
And you know who's gonna
climb over this site next?

43:45.356 --> 43:47.826
Congratulations, dude.

43:47.959 --> 43:50.228
You just shut yourself down.

43:51.496 --> 43:53.832
Did you run this by the boss?

43:55.566 --> 43:58.536
Yeah, I didn't think so.

44:00.171 --> 44:02.540
[both grunt]

44:03.408 --> 44:04.775
[Tommy sighs]

44:04.776 --> 44:08.279
<i>En este lado del río,</i>
I'm the fucking boss.

44:09.214 --> 44:10.515
[scoffs]

44:10.615 --> 44:14.952
If you're trying to send
a message, message received.

44:14.953 --> 44:17.154
Wait till you see
what we do with it.

44:17.155 --> 44:19.289
That's not the message.

44:19.290 --> 44:21.625
That's the warning.

44:21.626 --> 44:23.361
You're the message.

44:23.461 --> 44:25.163
<i>Saca la bolsa.</i>

44:26.231 --> 44:27.833
[Tommy groans]

44:31.102 --> 44:33.705
<i>♪ tense, suspenseful music ♪</i>

44:33.972 --> 44:36.407
<i>***</i>

44:39.277 --> 44:40.946
[Tommy groans]

44:44.816 --> 44:47.919
[engines start]

45:01.166 --> 45:03.401
<i>♪ somber music ♪</i>

45:03.668 --> 45:06.037
<i>***</i>

45:08.239 --> 45:10.141
[sniffles]

45:17.015 --> 45:19.584
[crying]

45:31.596 --> 45:34.499
[hyperventilating]

45:39.370 --> 45:41.705
[crying]

45:41.706 --> 45:44.241
- [vehicle approaching]
- [panting]

45:44.242 --> 45:47.112
[dog barking]

45:47.245 --> 45:48.847
[gasps]

45:51.783 --> 45:53.717
Fuck.
[sniffles]

45:53.718 --> 45:55.954
[crying]

46:04.595 --> 46:06.464
Hey, Jefe.

46:10.101 --> 46:12.270
Ariana?

46:13.972 --> 46:15.373
[crying]

46:24.782 --> 46:26.051
Fuck.

46:26.151 --> 46:27.886
[sighs]

46:27.986 --> 46:29.087
[grunts]

46:36.962 --> 46:39.865
[cries]

46:42.233 --> 46:43.267
Hey.

46:43.268 --> 46:45.470
- I'll be out in a minute.
- Sorry.

46:45.570 --> 46:47.104
Guess we haven't reached
the "barge in the bathroom"

46:47.105 --> 46:49.007
- part of the relationship.
- And we never will.

46:49.140 --> 46:51.641
A girl needs a certain amount
of mystery.

46:51.642 --> 46:53.879
Fair enough.

46:55.480 --> 46:57.682
[sighs]

46:57.815 --> 46:59.517
[pants]

47:15.366 --> 47:17.667
[sighs]

47:17.668 --> 47:19.905
[Jefe panting]

47:41.392 --> 47:43.228
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

47:43.494 --> 47:45.630
<i>***</i>

47:48.466 --> 47:50.601
Hey.

47:52.971 --> 47:54.405
Tough day?

47:55.340 --> 47:57.075
Very.

47:58.209 --> 47:59.677
I'm sorry.

48:02.080 --> 48:03.748
Me, too.

48:05.016 --> 48:07.652
This is too soon, isn't it?

48:09.854 --> 48:11.356
Yeah.

48:15.893 --> 48:17.194
Should I leave?

48:17.195 --> 48:19.797
I didn't say leave.

48:26.371 --> 48:29.440
I'm not trying
to replace him, Ariana.

48:29.540 --> 48:33.111
Yes, you are,
and I'm letting you.

48:34.579 --> 48:37.182
I'm letting you fill that place
in my heart.

48:37.983 --> 48:39.150
[inhales sharply]

48:39.985 --> 48:41.419
But to let you in, I...

48:41.519 --> 48:42.820
I need to move him out,

48:42.920 --> 48:44.855
which means saying goodbye.

48:45.790 --> 48:47.925
Even though
he's already gone, I...

48:50.895 --> 48:52.830
...have to say goodbye
in my heart.

48:56.501 --> 48:58.569
What can I do to help?

49:00.405 --> 49:02.507
I don't know.

49:02.640 --> 49:04.142
[sniffles]

49:04.976 --> 49:07.578
I've never done this before.

49:23.128 --> 49:24.795
Where was this?

49:26.464 --> 49:28.233
On Brazos.

49:29.100 --> 49:30.401
It's a nice boat.

49:31.269 --> 49:32.870
Luis bought it.

49:33.638 --> 49:36.007
And then the crash of 2020.

49:36.774 --> 49:37.807
Then he sold it.

49:37.808 --> 49:41.579
But it was fun, fast.

49:43.681 --> 49:45.482
Where was the wedding?

49:45.483 --> 49:47.152
San Antonio.

49:47.252 --> 49:49.387
You ever been?

49:51.756 --> 49:53.558
I think maybe

49:53.658 --> 49:56.761
the most magical city
in the world.

49:57.562 --> 49:59.397
River weaves
through the middle of it

49:59.530 --> 50:01.232
like someplace in Italy.

50:01.366 --> 50:03.434
[both chuckle softly]

50:06.371 --> 50:09.040
You look beautiful.

50:09.907 --> 50:11.742
Yeah, well,

50:11.876 --> 50:15.812
that was a baby
and a thousand heartaches ago.

50:15.813 --> 50:18.482
I was the baby then.

50:18.483 --> 50:20.051
[chuckles]

50:20.151 --> 50:22.819
He's being a better sport
about that than I would've been.

50:22.820 --> 50:26.656
Hey, if you're lucky enough
to have a reception with me,

50:26.657 --> 50:28.259
I will put the cake
wherever I want

50:28.393 --> 50:29.927
and you will say "Thank you."

50:30.061 --> 50:31.495
Yes, ma'am. Thank you.

50:31.496 --> 50:33.898
That's right.
Start practicing now.

50:34.031 --> 50:36.167
[laughs]

50:38.569 --> 50:41.005
You two were a beautiful couple.

50:46.577 --> 50:48.246
Thank you.

50:49.180 --> 50:50.615
You were.

50:51.516 --> 50:53.084
For this.

50:53.918 --> 50:55.653
Thank you.

50:56.854 --> 50:59.189
I'll walk through every memory
with you, if you want.

50:59.190 --> 51:01.459
Every one.

51:06.197 --> 51:07.665
I do.

51:23.781 --> 51:25.316
Oh, wow.

51:25.416 --> 51:26.750
- Okay, give me that.
- No.

51:26.751 --> 51:28.084
- I think I like this one.
- Okay, Cooper, no.

51:28.085 --> 51:29.386
- No, this is my favorite.
- No.

51:29.387 --> 51:30.521
- Just give me.
- This one's the best.

51:30.621 --> 51:33.191
- Cooper! [laughs]
- [groans]

51:54.379 --> 51:56.614
[Dale sighs]

51:57.448 --> 51:58.716
Yeah?

51:58.816 --> 52:01.352
- Hello, sir. Is Ainsley here?
- You don't know?

52:01.486 --> 52:03.488
Don't know... what?

52:03.588 --> 52:05.122
If she's here.

52:07.225 --> 52:08.493
I sure hope she's here.

52:08.593 --> 52:11.128
Yeah, but you don't know.
[sniffles]

52:11.229 --> 52:15.733
So you just decided
to fucking drop by.

52:16.667 --> 52:20.905
- Yeah, she told me to swing by.
- Oh, so you do know she's here.

52:22.907 --> 52:24.309
Unless she left.

52:24.409 --> 52:26.677
Why would she leave
if she told you to come over?

52:29.614 --> 52:30.947
[sighs]
Sir, I-I don't know what--

52:30.948 --> 52:32.282
Look, if you know she's here,
just say

52:32.283 --> 52:33.318
"I would like to see Ainsley"

52:33.418 --> 52:34.784
or "May I see Ainsley?"

52:34.785 --> 52:36.721
It makes no fucking sense
to ask if she's here.

52:36.854 --> 52:39.122
You know she's here.
I know she's here.

52:39.123 --> 52:41.759
Everyone in this fucking house
knows she's here.

52:43.194 --> 52:44.795
Now what you gonna do?

52:45.896 --> 52:47.365
What you gonna do, boy?

52:50.535 --> 52:53.970
[laughing]
I'm just fucking with you.

52:53.971 --> 52:56.040
Come on. Come on in.

52:56.140 --> 52:57.542
It's all right.

52:57.642 --> 53:00.611
Your fucking face. "Ooh."

53:02.046 --> 53:03.414
[sighs]

53:03.548 --> 53:04.749
[spoon clinking]

53:04.849 --> 53:06.816
- Evening, Mrs. Norris.
- Hello, Ryder.

53:06.817 --> 53:10.355
- What you making?
- Oh, I'm just clarifying butter.

53:10.455 --> 53:12.890
Well, that smells amazing.
I could eat a whole bowl of it.

53:13.023 --> 53:15.158
If you did, you wouldn't have
that little peanut-butt

53:15.159 --> 53:17.228
- for long.
- [spoon clinking]

53:17.362 --> 53:19.597
She's upstairs.

53:20.498 --> 53:21.532
Thank you.

53:21.632 --> 53:23.301
[spoon clinking]

53:38.148 --> 53:39.750
[Ainsley]
It's open.

53:42.520 --> 53:44.655
Close the door.

53:44.755 --> 53:46.757
See the chair
beneath the lights?

53:46.857 --> 53:48.224
Yeah?

53:48.225 --> 53:50.727
Sit.

53:50.728 --> 53:52.730
[Ryder sighs]

53:55.600 --> 53:58.068
You're gonna want
to take off that itchy shirt.

53:58.869 --> 54:00.671
Doesn't itch.

54:02.873 --> 54:04.709
You take it off.

54:07.044 --> 54:08.813
[sighs]
And the boots?

54:08.913 --> 54:11.115
There's no reason to stop there.

54:20.825 --> 54:23.060
- Are you done?
- Yeah.

54:29.767 --> 54:31.067
[sighs]

54:31.068 --> 54:34.404
I went to the trouble
of wrapping your present.

54:34.405 --> 54:35.840
I think I love you.

54:35.973 --> 54:37.475
You think?

54:37.575 --> 54:38.942
I know.

54:38.943 --> 54:40.811
That's better.

54:40.911 --> 54:42.847
What you did
for those old folks,

54:42.947 --> 54:45.582
it meant the world to them.

54:45.583 --> 54:48.018
<i>[Tanner Usrey's "Destiny"
playing]</i>

54:51.422 --> 54:53.157
Meant the world to me.

54:53.290 --> 54:55.393
I can do it again, you know.

54:55.493 --> 54:56.994
Whatever you need.

54:57.094 --> 54:58.928
I might take you up on that.

54:58.929 --> 55:04.134
<i>♪ Where the boys in the corner
keep on staring me down... ♪</i>

55:04.234 --> 55:06.136
Deal's a deal.

55:06.236 --> 55:11.008
<i>♪ And ain't nothing make me feel
the way that I feel with you ♪</i>

55:11.108 --> 55:13.744
<i>♪ You're my destiny ♪</i>

55:15.279 --> 55:16.714
<i>♪ Oh, my destiny... ♪</i>

55:16.814 --> 55:18.449
Unwrap me.

55:20.050 --> 55:22.219
<i>***</i>

55:35.966 --> 55:38.001
<i>[Alex Arellano's "El Gato Negro"
playing inside]</i>

55:38.002 --> 55:40.270
<i>[man singing in Spanish]</i>

55:46.577 --> 55:48.746
[lively chatter]

56:16.373 --> 56:18.909
<i>***</i>

56:43.000 --> 56:44.869
[door closes]

56:51.175 --> 56:53.143
You probably think
I have your head covered

56:53.243 --> 56:55.480
so you don't know where you are.

56:57.281 --> 56:59.283
I don't care if you know.

57:00.518 --> 57:03.621
Because you won't live to tell
anyone what you saw anyway.

57:03.754 --> 57:05.956
[sighs]

57:07.625 --> 57:09.460
Your army,

57:09.560 --> 57:13.664
your special forces
trained Mexico's <i>policía</i>

57:13.798 --> 57:16.033
to combat the cartels.

57:18.603 --> 57:21.138
Taught us all sorts of tricks.

57:23.307 --> 57:24.875
This is one of them.

57:25.710 --> 57:29.046
I take away one of your senses,

57:29.146 --> 57:32.016
and it magnifies the others.

57:33.150 --> 57:34.652
Like sound.

57:40.390 --> 57:44.161
[whistling]

57:57.107 --> 57:58.909
- [grunts]
- [groaning]

58:00.310 --> 58:01.277
<i>¿Ves?</i>

58:01.278 --> 58:03.380
And everything is a surprise.

58:03.514 --> 58:06.016
All this pain magnified,

58:06.116 --> 58:08.553
because I took your sight.

58:09.353 --> 58:12.690
When someone is truly terrified,

58:12.790 --> 58:14.959
they lose feeling.

58:16.260 --> 58:17.862
They may scream in horror

58:17.962 --> 58:21.832
when you slice
into their stomach,

58:21.932 --> 58:23.167
but they can't feel it.

58:23.267 --> 58:25.335
No.

58:25.435 --> 58:27.404
The shock of seeing it,

58:27.538 --> 58:29.907
nah, it's too much.

58:31.676 --> 58:34.211
But when you can't see...

58:34.311 --> 58:36.413
ah...

58:37.181 --> 58:39.550
...then you feel everything.

58:39.650 --> 58:42.652
[Tommy screams]

58:42.653 --> 58:44.922
[groaning]

58:46.857 --> 58:48.491
<i>Eso.</i> You scream.

58:48.492 --> 58:52.597
From the pain, not the horror.

58:52.730 --> 58:55.032
I can make this last all night,

58:55.132 --> 58:56.801
and I will.

58:57.868 --> 59:00.571
[Tommy] How much product
did you fucking lose?

59:00.705 --> 59:02.607
What's the number you need, motherfucker?

59:02.740 --> 59:04.775
No, you had your chance
to negotiate.

59:04.875 --> 59:06.644
That's not why you're here.

59:06.744 --> 59:08.412
You're here so the one
who replaces you takes

59:08.512 --> 59:10.247
- the chance when he has it.
- [snaps fingers]

59:10.347 --> 59:12.849
<i>♪ soft, eerie music ♪</i>

59:12.850 --> 59:15.586
[gasoline sloshing]

59:16.621 --> 59:21.390
[Tommy groans]
Oh, goddamn it!

59:21.391 --> 59:23.392
Motherfucker. Fuck you!

59:23.393 --> 59:26.764
Fucking light me on fire,
you goddamn cocksucker.

59:26.864 --> 59:28.397
Fuck you!

59:28.398 --> 59:30.434
- Fuck me, huh?
- Yeah, fuck you.

59:30.534 --> 59:32.069
Okay.

59:32.169 --> 59:33.971
Okay, Tommy.

59:34.104 --> 59:35.840
Son of a...

59:36.674 --> 59:39.743
- No. I think...
- [coughing]

59:39.744 --> 59:41.711
...fuck you.

59:41.712 --> 59:46.450
- Fuck you, Tommy!
- [yelling] Oh, God!

59:46.550 --> 59:48.217
[yells, coughs]

59:48.218 --> 59:50.154
[groaning]

59:50.287 --> 59:52.657
[coughing]

59:53.557 --> 59:55.192
[sighs]

59:58.929 --> 01:00:00.564
<i>Listo.</i>

01:00:02.066 --> 01:00:05.169
<i>Más temprano,
cuando está más tranquilo.</i>

01:00:05.269 --> 01:00:07.672
<i>Mueve la van atras.
Cerca de las puertas.</i>

01:00:34.098 --> 01:00:36.166
One flick of this

01:00:36.266 --> 01:00:38.836
and it's goodbye to you...

01:00:39.636 --> 01:00:41.872
<i>...pinche</i> Tommy.

01:00:48.112 --> 01:00:50.247
[crickets chirping]

01:00:52.983 --> 01:00:54.483
[man speaking indistinctly
on TV]

01:00:54.484 --> 01:00:56.754
[footsteps approaching]

01:00:59.189 --> 01:01:00.524
You heard from Tommy?

01:01:00.624 --> 01:01:02.359
[grunts]

01:01:02.459 --> 01:01:03.560
Uh...

01:01:05.595 --> 01:01:07.064
No.

01:01:08.398 --> 01:01:09.867
Hmm.

01:01:09.967 --> 01:01:11.301
[sets phone down]

01:01:12.636 --> 01:01:15.272
He's not answering my calls.

01:01:17.341 --> 01:01:20.009
Did he, uh...
did he go back to Fort Worth?

01:01:20.010 --> 01:01:21.345
[sniffs, clears throat]

01:01:21.445 --> 01:01:23.981
'Cause you can't use a cell
in the ICU.

01:01:25.783 --> 01:01:26.951
Maybe that's it.

01:01:27.051 --> 01:01:28.719
Mm-hmm.

01:01:28.819 --> 01:01:30.587
<i>♪ ominous music ♪</i>

01:01:30.921 --> 01:01:33.090
<i>***</i>

01:01:42.499 --> 01:01:44.368
[grunts]

01:01:55.212 --> 01:01:56.580
[sniffles]

01:01:58.315 --> 01:02:00.050
What's wrong?

01:02:01.752 --> 01:02:03.153
Nothing.

01:02:03.921 --> 01:02:05.622
[sniffles]

01:02:05.756 --> 01:02:07.724
I'm happy.

01:02:09.093 --> 01:02:12.296
You sure don't sound happy.

01:02:15.465 --> 01:02:17.601
Have you ever done this before?

01:02:17.701 --> 01:02:20.536
I'd done about half of it.

01:02:20.537 --> 01:02:22.973
I'd barely even thought
of the other half.

01:02:23.107 --> 01:02:25.810
I mean like-like this.

01:02:25.910 --> 01:02:27.511
[sniffles]

01:02:27.611 --> 01:02:29.613
Sleeping together.

01:02:30.647 --> 01:02:32.016
No.

01:02:33.083 --> 01:02:34.852
Never.

01:02:38.022 --> 01:02:39.790
Me neither.

01:02:41.625 --> 01:02:42.926
[sniffles]

01:02:42.927 --> 01:02:44.862
Will you stay?

01:02:46.630 --> 01:02:48.265
The night?

01:02:50.567 --> 01:02:52.803
[sighs]
Your dad will kill me.

01:02:52.903 --> 01:02:54.671
I won't let him.

01:02:55.739 --> 01:02:59.176
Ainsley, he will kick
the shit out of me.

01:03:01.211 --> 01:03:03.113
[sniffles, chuckles]

01:03:03.213 --> 01:03:05.182
That's a possibility.

01:03:05.282 --> 01:03:06.716
[sniffles]

01:03:08.118 --> 01:03:09.719
Please.

01:03:10.720 --> 01:03:12.689
I don't want to be alone.

01:03:17.027 --> 01:03:19.296
[sighs, inhales deeply]

01:03:19.396 --> 01:03:21.832
I'll take my chances.

01:03:21.932 --> 01:03:23.667
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

01:03:23.934 --> 01:03:26.136
<i>***</i>

01:03:30.307 --> 01:03:31.876
[breathing heavily]

01:03:32.009 --> 01:03:33.510
[grunting]

01:03:33.610 --> 01:03:35.979
[panting]

01:03:35.980 --> 01:03:37.181
Hey.

01:03:37.314 --> 01:03:38.849
<i>- Huevón.</i>
- [door opens]

01:03:38.983 --> 01:03:41.284
<i>- Levántate.</i>
- [groans]

01:03:41.285 --> 01:03:42.920
- [door closes]
- [grunts]

01:03:46.123 --> 01:03:47.591
<i>Estamos cerrado.</i>

01:03:47.691 --> 01:03:49.325
<i>Bueno.</i>

01:03:49.326 --> 01:03:50.995
<i>-¿Hay gente afuera?
- Sí.</i>

01:03:51.095 --> 01:03:52.362
<i>Pero están saliendo.</i>

01:03:54.298 --> 01:03:55.999
<i>¿No quieres una pistola?</i>

01:03:56.000 --> 01:03:57.667
<i>No.</i>

01:03:57.767 --> 01:04:01.038
<i>Es un cuchillo para este joto.</i>

01:04:02.006 --> 01:04:03.707
- [gunshots]
- [thudding]

01:04:03.840 --> 01:04:05.075
<i>¡Vamos, vamos, vamos,
vamos, vamos!</i>

01:04:05.175 --> 01:04:06.675
<i>[men shouting in Spanish]</i>

01:04:06.676 --> 01:04:08.712
<i>♪ low, tense music ♪</i>

01:04:08.979 --> 01:04:11.148
<i>***</i>

01:04:12.149 --> 01:04:13.717
- [gunshots]
- [thudding]

01:04:13.817 --> 01:04:16.053
- [indistinct shouting]
- [gunshots]

01:04:16.153 --> 01:04:17.486
- [groaning]
- [thudding]

01:04:17.487 --> 01:04:19.022
[gunshots]

01:04:19.023 --> 01:04:20.356
- [groaning]
- [glass shattering]

01:04:20.357 --> 01:04:22.059
[Tommy breathing heavily]

01:04:22.326 --> 01:04:25.462
<i>***</i>

01:04:33.737 --> 01:04:35.204
[gunshots]

01:04:35.205 --> 01:04:36.773
- [man groans]
- [Tommy gasps]

01:04:37.741 --> 01:04:40.410
[gunshots]

01:04:41.845 --> 01:04:43.580
[Tommy breathing heavily]

01:04:43.847 --> 01:04:45.782
<i>***</i>

01:04:50.754 --> 01:04:52.957
[footsteps approaching]

01:04:54.358 --> 01:04:56.560
[breathing heavily]

01:04:58.895 --> 01:05:00.097
[Tommy shuddering]

01:05:00.197 --> 01:05:01.932
[Gallino]
Knock, knock.

01:05:13.010 --> 01:05:14.678
<i>Suéltalo.</i>

01:05:15.512 --> 01:05:17.447
[knife opens]

01:05:18.582 --> 01:05:20.050
[snips]

01:05:22.752 --> 01:05:24.288
[snips]

01:05:29.293 --> 01:05:30.860
[snips]

01:05:30.961 --> 01:05:32.997
<i>Córtalo, coño.</i>

01:05:33.097 --> 01:05:34.999
<i>Córtalo.</i>

01:05:39.803 --> 01:05:41.638
[hisses]

01:05:42.472 --> 01:05:44.474
[groans]

01:05:44.608 --> 01:05:45.809
[sighs]

01:05:45.909 --> 01:05:47.511
[clinks]

01:05:48.612 --> 01:05:51.215
I'd offer you one, but
I'm not sure it's a good idea.

01:05:52.182 --> 01:05:54.518
That's all right.
I'll take my chances.

01:05:54.784 --> 01:05:56.886
<i>***</i>

01:06:06.430 --> 01:06:08.732
Be careful now.

01:06:14.404 --> 01:06:16.173
[lighter clicks shut]

01:06:16.273 --> 01:06:17.940
You good?

01:06:17.941 --> 01:06:20.444
Yeah, I'm just fucking dandy.

01:06:21.345 --> 01:06:22.779
You will be.

01:06:23.913 --> 01:06:27.117
Jimenez, he did not understand
what I understand.

01:06:28.352 --> 01:06:31.921
Which is that we must coexist.

01:06:32.856 --> 01:06:35.825
There are times
where you lose things--

01:06:35.925 --> 01:06:37.126
trucks, planes--

01:06:37.127 --> 01:06:38.695
and there are times
I lose things--

01:06:38.795 --> 01:06:40.997
trucks, planes, merchandise.

01:06:41.098 --> 01:06:42.699
That's just business.

01:06:42.799 --> 01:06:44.201
So...

01:06:45.069 --> 01:06:47.237
...how do we get back
to where it was

01:06:47.371 --> 01:06:49.873
so we can...

01:06:50.006 --> 01:06:51.741
so we can coexist?

01:06:52.809 --> 01:06:54.009
Well,

01:06:54.010 --> 01:06:57.047
you understand,
above everything else...

01:06:58.382 --> 01:07:01.785
...nobody can escalate this
higher than we can.

01:07:02.786 --> 01:07:04.353
And I'm guessing you know that.

01:07:04.354 --> 01:07:06.623
Otherwise you wouldn't be here.

01:07:08.492 --> 01:07:10.594
So...

01:07:10.727 --> 01:07:13.097
you want to go back...

01:07:14.731 --> 01:07:17.134
...stay out of our fucking way.

01:07:18.202 --> 01:07:20.036
Or I go sit with every CEO

01:07:20.137 --> 01:07:22.606
of every oil company
in the Permian Basin

01:07:22.706 --> 01:07:26.376
and we build the DEA
a fucking city.

01:07:30.680 --> 01:07:32.681
For free.

01:07:32.682 --> 01:07:34.218
It ain't nothing for us to throw

01:07:34.318 --> 01:07:36.920
ten or 20 billion dollars
at a problem.

01:07:37.020 --> 01:07:38.588
Nothing.

01:07:39.656 --> 01:07:43.093
Now, you got a couple
of sheriffs and some judges

01:07:43.193 --> 01:07:45.962
and some mayors
along the border there.

01:07:46.096 --> 01:07:49.466
We've got ex-presidents
on our boards.

01:07:49.599 --> 01:07:52.202
- And senators.
- Mm.

01:07:52.969 --> 01:07:54.904
Hell, Chevron named
a fucking oil tanker

01:07:55.004 --> 01:07:57.107
after Condoleezza Rice.

01:07:57.207 --> 01:07:59.041
Here's the thing.

01:07:59.042 --> 01:08:02.279
You have no idea
who you're fucking with.

01:08:03.079 --> 01:08:04.614
And if you kill me

01:08:04.748 --> 01:08:06.916
and hang me
off a goddamn bridge,

01:08:07.016 --> 01:08:09.385
guess what happens next.

01:08:09.386 --> 01:08:12.122
We blow up the fucking bridge.

01:08:12.222 --> 01:08:14.757
We're the last bear
you want to poke, bud,

01:08:14.758 --> 01:08:17.794
because we have unlimited funds

01:08:17.894 --> 01:08:20.096
and unlimited connections.

01:08:20.197 --> 01:08:21.498
[Gallino]
We have...

01:08:21.598 --> 01:08:23.133
we have the same senators,
my friend,

01:08:23.233 --> 01:08:26.970
the same presidents,
and we have the same enemies.

01:08:27.771 --> 01:08:29.773
You and I have the same enemies.

01:08:29.873 --> 01:08:32.276
And there's nothing
that you have that I don't have.

01:08:32.376 --> 01:08:33.977
And, well, you don't want
the world to know

01:08:34.077 --> 01:08:36.079
how you make
the thing you sell...

01:08:37.080 --> 01:08:41.251
...and I don't want the world to
know how I do the thing I sell.

01:08:42.319 --> 01:08:45.222
The world is a better place
if we are friends.

01:08:46.055 --> 01:08:47.724
I get that.

01:08:48.492 --> 01:08:50.494
But we ain't ever gonna be
friends.

01:08:50.594 --> 01:08:51.627
What's that?

01:08:51.628 --> 01:08:53.330
We ain't ever gonna be friends.

01:08:53.430 --> 01:08:55.165
Oh, yeah,
we're gonna be friends.

01:08:55.265 --> 01:08:56.833
Yeah, we'll see about that.

01:08:56.966 --> 01:08:59.135
You need to avoid us
like the goddamn plague

01:08:59.236 --> 01:09:00.737
and we'll do the same.

01:09:01.538 --> 01:09:03.707
And if our paths ever do cross,

01:09:03.840 --> 01:09:06.643
then everybody's
gonna be real friendly

01:09:06.743 --> 01:09:10.046
and everybody's gonna be
real forgiving.

01:09:10.880 --> 01:09:12.649
Well, that's advice
we both should take.

01:09:12.749 --> 01:09:15.419
- It's a good start. Mm.
- [phone buzzing]

01:09:17.954 --> 01:09:20.357
Mm. Police chief.

01:09:20.457 --> 01:09:22.325
We should go.
The police are here.

01:09:22.326 --> 01:09:24.928
<i>Vamos a irnos
para afuera por atrás.</i>

01:09:26.330 --> 01:09:28.365
Go on. We should go.

01:09:29.233 --> 01:09:30.700
Come on. Okay.

01:09:30.800 --> 01:09:32.536
[strains]

01:09:32.636 --> 01:09:33.770
[groans]

01:09:35.772 --> 01:09:36.940
Oh, this way.

01:09:37.040 --> 01:09:38.208
- Going out the back.
- [door opens]

01:09:40.277 --> 01:09:41.545
[Tommy groans softly]

01:09:43.380 --> 01:09:45.814
Hold on, hold on.
Wait for me, amigo.

01:09:45.815 --> 01:09:48.117
I got you. Watch your step here.

01:09:49.786 --> 01:09:51.955
[Tommy groaning]

01:09:53.223 --> 01:09:56.125
<i>-¿Estamos bien?</i>
- [man] <i>Todo bien.</i>

01:09:59.529 --> 01:10:01.698
- Watch your step.
- [grunts]

01:10:01.798 --> 01:10:04.032
- You got a cell phone?
- Yeah.

01:10:04.033 --> 01:10:05.334
Call somebody you trust.

01:10:05.335 --> 01:10:06.669
Tell them to bring you
some clothes.

01:10:06.670 --> 01:10:07.937
You can't walk out of here
like that.

01:10:08.272 --> 01:10:10.440
<i>***</i>

01:10:16.580 --> 01:10:18.181
[Gallino]
One more.

01:10:21.518 --> 01:10:22.886
Okay, there's
a washroom up here.

01:10:22.986 --> 01:10:24.053
[Tommy grunts]

01:10:24.153 --> 01:10:26.256
Make sure it's clear.

01:10:29.359 --> 01:10:30.760
Yeah, we're good.

01:10:30.860 --> 01:10:33.430
All right. Right there.

01:10:33.563 --> 01:10:36.266
You know
we own land where you drill.

01:10:36.366 --> 01:10:38.033
Yeah.

01:10:38.034 --> 01:10:39.603
There's no money
in that land, though.

01:10:39.703 --> 01:10:40.604
[exhales]

01:10:40.737 --> 01:10:43.440
Money's beneath the surface.

01:10:46.476 --> 01:10:50.113
I'd like to talk to you about
that when you have some time.

01:10:51.781 --> 01:10:53.517
I'll make the time.

01:10:53.617 --> 01:10:56.986
There you go.
Who says we can't be friends?

01:10:57.120 --> 01:10:58.288
We make enough money,

01:10:58.422 --> 01:11:00.457
we're gonna be
real good friends.

01:11:04.861 --> 01:11:07.464
There's no future
in the product you sell.

01:11:07.564 --> 01:11:10.800
I'm more curious about
the product you sell.

01:11:10.934 --> 01:11:13.402
[exhales] Mine's running out
of future, too.

01:11:13.403 --> 01:11:16.105
Maybe so, but there's
still some future left.

01:11:16.205 --> 01:11:18.308
Washroom's in the back.
Call your friend.

01:11:18.408 --> 01:11:20.810
Stay here till he comes.
<i>Vámonos.</i>

01:11:20.910 --> 01:11:23.146
Let's go.

01:11:23.246 --> 01:11:25.114
Here.

01:11:25.214 --> 01:11:27.050
Keep the smokes.

01:11:28.818 --> 01:11:31.054
I'd give you my lighter, but...

01:11:31.855 --> 01:11:33.557
...belonged to my father.

01:11:35.625 --> 01:11:37.494
<i>♪ slow, ominous music ♪</i>

01:11:37.761 --> 01:11:40.430
<i>***</i>

01:11:51.741 --> 01:11:54.010
[train whistle blowing]

01:12:04.187 --> 01:12:06.356
[groans]

01:12:23.039 --> 01:12:26.309
Hey, I'm gonna send you a pin.
Come pick me up.

01:12:27.143 --> 01:12:29.345
<i>***</i>

01:12:43.359 --> 01:12:46.730
There ain't gonna be
no hiding that shiner.

01:12:48.398 --> 01:12:50.934
I'll just tell her
I had a car wreck.

01:12:51.901 --> 01:12:53.737
You need to go
to the hospital for your leg.

01:12:53.837 --> 01:12:55.371
No fucking telling
what was on that thing.

01:12:55.472 --> 01:12:57.506
[coughs] Oh, I'm not going
to the fucking hospital.

01:12:57.507 --> 01:12:59.075
Well, I'm just saying,
think about--

01:12:59.175 --> 01:13:01.044
D-Dale, I'm not going
to the fucking hospital.

01:13:01.144 --> 01:13:04.180
Fine, I'll shut up.
[exhales]

01:13:08.384 --> 01:13:09.586
Let me at least get you a doctor

01:13:09.686 --> 01:13:11.120
to meet you at the camp
in the afternoon.

01:13:11.220 --> 01:13:12.321
Let me do that for you, Tommy.

01:13:12.422 --> 01:13:14.123
And tell him what?

01:13:14.257 --> 01:13:16.059
Tell him...

01:13:16.159 --> 01:13:18.061
tell him that you shot yourself
with a nail gun

01:13:18.161 --> 01:13:20.564
while you was building
a fucking sundeck.

01:13:20.664 --> 01:13:22.098
- I don't know.
- [both laugh]

01:13:22.231 --> 01:13:24.768
- I don't fucking...
- [coughing]

01:13:28.805 --> 01:13:31.373
You all right?

01:13:31.374 --> 01:13:32.476
[groans]

01:13:32.576 --> 01:13:35.378
Take it easy, take it easy.

01:13:41.417 --> 01:13:43.487
How are you, uh...

01:13:45.421 --> 01:13:48.091
...how are you doing,
you know, up here?

01:13:48.191 --> 01:13:49.993
[lighter clicks]

01:13:51.895 --> 01:13:53.129
What?

01:13:53.229 --> 01:13:55.898
You mean mentally?

01:13:55.899 --> 01:13:58.468
Yeah, something like that. Sure.

01:14:00.937 --> 01:14:02.772
[sighs]

01:14:02.872 --> 01:14:04.941
I think I'm gonna
start drinking again.

01:14:05.041 --> 01:14:06.976
<i>♪ slow, atmospheric music ♪</i>

01:14:07.243 --> 01:14:09.077
<i>***</i>

01:14:09.078 --> 01:14:11.347
[scoffs]

01:14:11.481 --> 01:14:13.783
[chuckles]

01:14:14.551 --> 01:14:18.021
[train whistle blows]

01:14:30.800 --> 01:14:32.936
<i>***</i>

01:15:02.298 --> 01:15:04.433
<i>***</i>

01:15:32.495 --> 01:15:34.631
<i>***</i>

01:15:37.567 --> 01:15:40.269
[Angela]
Why you sleeping on the couch?

01:15:40.369 --> 01:15:42.505
I didn't want
to wake you up, honey.

01:15:44.708 --> 01:15:46.676
What happened to your face?

01:15:48.211 --> 01:15:49.779
I had a car wreck.

01:15:49.879 --> 01:15:51.615
Bullshit.

01:15:51.715 --> 01:15:54.150
You would've called me
if you had a car wreck.

01:15:55.218 --> 01:15:57.253
- Sit down.
- Don't tell me what to do.

01:15:57.386 --> 01:16:01.257
Oh, honey,
please just sit down beside me.

01:16:01.357 --> 01:16:02.792
[groans]

01:16:02.892 --> 01:16:04.794
This better be fucking good.

01:16:08.865 --> 01:16:10.266
Honey?

01:16:13.436 --> 01:16:16.239
There are gonna be things
that I can't tell you.

01:16:16.339 --> 01:16:19.142
That you can't tell me?

01:16:20.176 --> 01:16:21.811
Just trust me.

01:16:25.248 --> 01:16:27.450
One thing I can tell you...

01:16:29.085 --> 01:16:32.856
...is that my whole life
passed before my eyes...

01:16:33.690 --> 01:16:35.591
[Angela sighs]

01:16:35.692 --> 01:16:37.927
...and all I saw was you.

01:16:50.373 --> 01:16:52.074
I'm-a make you breakfast.

01:16:52.075 --> 01:16:54.277
- Oh.
- You hungry?

01:16:54.377 --> 01:16:56.179
[chuckles]
No, babe.

01:16:56.279 --> 01:16:58.848
Blueberry pancakes.

01:16:58.982 --> 01:17:00.082
Does that sound good?

01:17:00.083 --> 01:17:02.518
[chuckles]
Okay.

01:17:02.618 --> 01:17:04.487
That sounds great.

01:17:04.587 --> 01:17:06.322
<i>♪ somber music ♪</i>

01:17:06.589 --> 01:17:09.192
<i>***</i>

01:17:10.493 --> 01:17:12.528
[Angela sniffles]

01:17:12.628 --> 01:17:14.230
[sighs]

01:17:18.267 --> 01:17:22.038
[crying]

01:17:33.616 --> 01:17:34.884
[sighs]

01:17:35.018 --> 01:17:36.686
[sniffles]

01:17:36.786 --> 01:17:39.022
[clears throat]

01:17:45.294 --> 01:17:47.295
[clears throat]

01:17:47.296 --> 01:17:50.233
- [groaning]
- [clattering]

01:17:57.373 --> 01:17:59.508
- Morning, Daddy.
- Oh.

01:17:59.608 --> 01:18:01.176
Morning, baby.

01:18:01.177 --> 01:18:02.846
Morning, sir.

01:18:05.681 --> 01:18:08.183
[sighs]

01:18:08.184 --> 01:18:10.920
I don't have
the fucking energy for this.

01:18:11.020 --> 01:18:13.222
[indistinct chatter]

01:18:26.202 --> 01:18:28.071
<i>♪ slow, eerie music ♪</i>

01:18:28.337 --> 01:18:30.473
<i>***</i>

01:18:50.693 --> 01:18:53.629
<i>***</i>

01:19:08.978 --> 01:19:11.180
<i>***</i>

01:19:21.657 --> 01:19:24.493
You better run, buddy.

01:19:28.998 --> 01:19:32.168
They kill coyotes around here.

01:19:52.788 --> 01:19:54.557
<i>♪ slow, eerie music ♪</i>

01:19:54.891 --> 01:19:57.060
<i>***</i>

01:20:32.028 --> 01:20:35.064
<i>***</i>
